HEADWORD: Pyrography
<hw>Py*rog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pyro-</ets> + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety> <def>A process of
printing, ornamenting, or carving, by burning with heated instruments.
One variant is <stype>wood burning</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

